'''Matěj Kovář''' (born 17 May 2000) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

Kovář joined the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United youth system]] in 2018, from Czech club [[1. FC Slovácko]]. He spent time on loan at [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]], where he made his senior debut, [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] and [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]. A former Czech youth international, Kovář represented his country from [[Czech Republic national under-18 football team|under-18]] to [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|under-21]] level.

==Club career==
===Manchester United===
Kovář began his career with [[1. FC Slovácko]] in his native Czech Republic, but moved to England to join [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in January 2018 at the age of 17.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Mark|last=Froggatt|title=Young goalkeeper joins United from FC Slovacko|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/matej-kovar-has-joined-manchester-united-from-fc-slovacko|website=Manchester United|date=31 January 2018|access-date=10 September 2020}}</ref> After being an unused substitute for the under-19s in a [[2017–18 UEFA Youth League]] match against rivals [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on 21 February 2018, he made his debut for the club's under-18s side in a 4–1 league win at home to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] three days later. He played in all but two of the team's remaining matches that season, replacing Alex Fojtíček as first-choice goalkeeper. Kovář was again the first-choice goalkeeper for the reserve team the following season, playing in 17 of their 22 league matches; he also played in six of the seven matches for the under-19s in the [[2018–19 UEFA Youth League]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Matej Kovar|url=http://www.redstat.co.uk/?PlayerNo=1784|website=redStat|access-date=11 September 2020}}</ref>

In 2019–20, he played in 11 of the 17 league matches the reserves played before the season was curtailed by the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom]], as well as all four matches they played in the [[2019–20 EFL Trophy]], in which they came up against the senior sides of the teams in [[EFL League One]] and [[EFL League Two|Two]]. His performances for the reserves earned him a new contract with the club, signed in October 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Adam|last=Marshall|title=Kovar signs new contract with United|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/matej-kovar-signs-new-contract-with-man-utd|website=Manchester United |date=9 October 2019|access-date=10 September 2020}}</ref> With the first team's qualification for the knockout phase of the [[2019–20 UEFA Europa League]] secure, manager [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]] selected a young team for their matchday 5 game against [[FC Astana|Astana]] in Kazakhstan on 28 November 2019; Kovář was named on the bench as back-up for [[Lee Grant (footballer, born 1983)|Lee Grant]], but did not play in the match.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Saj|last=Chowdhury|title=Astana 2–1 Manchester United: Solskjaer says youngsters 'knocking on door' of first team|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50508966|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=28 November 2019|access-date=10 September 2020}}</ref>

Ahead of the 2020–21 season, Kovář moved on loan to [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] in August 2020.<ref name="auto">{{Cite news|title=Matej Kovar: Manchester United keeper joins Swindon on loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53952459|website=BBC Sport|date=28 August 2020|access-date=10 September 2020}}</ref> He made his debut on 5 September 2020, in a 3–1 defeat against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] in the [[EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Match report: Swindon Town 1–3 Charlton Athletic|url=https://www.swindontownfc.co.uk/news/2020/september/match-report-swindon-town-1-3-charlton-athletic/|website=Swindon Town F.C.|date=5 September 2020|access-date=29 May 2022}}</ref> In January 2021, Kovář was recalled by Manchester United after making 21 appearances for Swindon.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester United Recall Goalkeeper Matej Kovar|url=https://www.swindontownfc.co.uk/news/2021/january/manchester-united-re-call-goalkeeper-matej-kovar/|website=[[Swindon Town F.C.]]|date=5 January 2021|access-date=6 January 2021}}</ref>

Kovář was named in United's final Premier League squad submitted after the end of the transfer deadline for the [[2021–22 Manchester United F.C. season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Adam|last=Marshall|title=United's Premier League squad confirmed|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-premier-league-squad-confirmed-for-2021-22|website=Manchester United|date=10 September 2021|access-date=12 September 2021 }}</ref> On 31 January 2022, Kovář signed a new contract with United until June 2023 and moved on loan to [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovar signs deal and moves on loan |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/matej-kovar-joins-burton-albion-on-loan-on-31-january-2022 |website=Manchester United|date=31 January 2022|access-date=1 February 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Evan|last=Draycott|title=Burton Albion Sign Goalkeeper Matej Kovar on Loan from Manchester United|url=https://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/news/2022/january/3101-kovar/|date=31 January 2022|access-date=1 February 2022|website=BurtonAlbionFC.co.uk|publisher=Burton Albion}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60208264|title=Burton Albion sign Harry Chapman, Sam Hughes, Christian Saydee and Matej Kovar|work=BBC Sport|date=31 January 2022|access-date=28 May 2022}}</ref>

On 9 September 2022, Kovář moved on loan to Czech club [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sparta.cz/cs/clanek/matej-kovar-prichazi-na-hostovani-39930|title=Matěj Kovář přichází na hostování|work=[[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]|date=9 September 2022|access-date=9 September 2022|language=cs}}</ref> He made his debut on 10 September 2022, in a 2–2 away draw against [[FK Teplice]] in the [[Czech First League]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Pavel|last=Dosadil|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-spici-medved-hned-nasadil-golmana-rudych-dablu-moje-minela-omlouva-se-za-dalsi-plichtu-3613419|title=Spící medvěd hned nasadil gólmana Rudých ďáblů. Moje minela, omlouvá se za další plichtu|website=sport.cz|date=10 September 2022|access-date=11 September 2022|language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref> Kovář helped the club to win its first championship title since 2014.<ref name = "title">{{Cite news|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|date=23 May 2023|access-date=23 May 2023|title=Sparta v euforii! Remíza na Slovácku odstartovala mistrovské oslavy|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-sparta-v-euforii-remiza-na-slovacku-odstartovala-mistrovske-oslavy-4229432 |website=[[Seznam.cz|Sport.cz]]|language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref> He was awarded as the goalkeeper of the [[2022–23 Czech First League|2022–23]] season by League Football Association (LFA).<ref name=":0">{{Cite press release |url=https://www.lfafotbal.cz/clanek/628-brankarem-sezony-spartan-kovar-mezi-obranci-uspel-jeho-spoluhrac-srensen |title=Brankářem sezony sparťan Kovář, mezi obránci uspěl jeho spoluhráč Sørensen |website=lfafotbal.cz|publisher=League Football Association|date=24 May 2023|access-date=13 September 2023|language=cs}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 15 August 2023, Kovář signed a four-year contract with German [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Vacek|first=Jan|date=15 August 2023|access-date=15 August 2023|title=Kovář už patří Leverkusenu: Nejlepší cesta, těším se na Hložka a Schicka|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-zahranici-nemecko-bundesliga/435086/kovar-uz-patri-leverkusenu-nejlepsi-cesta-tesim-se-na-hlozka-a-schicka.html|website=[[Blesk]]|language=cs|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]}}</ref> A transfer fee of up to £7.7 million, including add-ons, was agreed between United and Leverkusen.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man Utd net £7.7m from Kovar deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/c4n0gdjqjzzo |website=BBC Sport|date=15 August 2023 |access-date=18 August 2023}}</ref>

===PSV===
On 15 July 2025, Kovář joined Dutch [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on loan, with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Malý|first=Jan|date=15 July 2025|access-date=15 July 2025|title=Hotovo. Reprezentační jednička jde do Nizozemska|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-evropske-ligy-hotovo-reprezentacni-jednicka-jde-do-nizozemska-5262563|website=Sport.cz|language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref>

On 13 January 2026, Kovář signed a permanent contract with PSV until June 2030.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Mach|first=Tomáš|date=13 January 2026|access-date=13 January 2026|title=Kovář přestoupil do PSV|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-evropske-ligy-kovar-prestoupil-do-psv-5371524|website=Sport.cz|language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref>

==International career==
Kovář has represented the Czech Republic at [[Czech Republic national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Czech Republic national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Czech Republic national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|under-21]] youth levels.<ref name=ntprofile>{{cite web|url=https://repre.fotbal.cz/hrac/hraci/16332953|title=Matěj Kovář Reprezentace|website=Fotbal.cz|access-date=29 March 2023}}</ref> He was a member of the Czech squad at the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] in March 2021,<ref>{{cite web|title=Greenwood out of under-21 European Championship|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/mason-greenwood-pulls-out-of-under-21-european-championship|publisher=Manchester United|date=23 March 2021|access-date=29 May 2022}}</ref> but did not make any appearances in the tournament.<ref name=ntprofile/> He made his debut for the under-21 team in September 2021 against [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Confidence boosting back-to-back clean sheets for Matej Kovar|url=https://www.unitedinfocus.com/news/matej-kovar-gets-back-to-back-clean-sheets-for-czech-republic-under-21s/|website=unitedinfocus.com|date=September 2021|access-date=29 May 2022}}</ref>

Kovář was first called up to the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic senior team]] on 8 September 2021 for a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] after [[Tomáš Vaclík]] suffered an injury.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Adam|last=Marshall|title=First senior call-up for Kovar|url= https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/first-senior-czech-republic-call-up-for-matej-kovar-september-2021|website=Manchester United|date=8 September 2021|access-date=8 September 2021}}</ref> He debuted on 26 March 2024 in a friendly match against [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=S koučem Haškem vítězná premiéra i na domácí půdě. Čeští fotbalisté na Letné udolali Arménii 2:1|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/zive-cesti-fotbaliste-hraji-poprve-pod-koucem-haskem-doma-na-letne-hosti-armenii_2403261900_rej|website=[[Czech Radio]]|date=26 March 2024|access-date=27 March 2024|language=cs}}</ref> On 29 May 2024, Kovář was included in the final Czech squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]],<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ryan|last=Hancock|title=Czech Republic Euro 2024 squad: Ivan Hasek's full team|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/czech-republic-euro-2024-squad-team-players-line-up-germany|website=[[FourFourTwo]]|date=21 September 2023|access-date=13 June 2024}}</ref> making his competitive debut in a 1–2 loss against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] which led the Czech Republic to be eliminated from group stage.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Dominik|last=Duffek|title=Kovářův nečekaný debut: Připravený jsem vždy. Tondovi nic za vinu nedávám|trans-title=Kovář's unexpected debut: I'm always ready. I don't blame Tondo|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2024/matej-kovar-cesko-turecko-nahradnik-debut-stanek-zraneni.A240627_095710_euro-2024_duff|newspaper=Mladá fronta Dnes |date=27 June 2024|access-date=24 July 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

